<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870403-0102 </DOCNO><HL> Britton Lee to Post Loss</HL><DD> 04/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BLII </IN><DATELINE> LOS GATOS, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Britton Lee Inc. said it expects to post a loss for the first quarter on lower revenue because of delayed order completions.    The maker of computer systems didn't estimate the amount of the loss or specify revenue figures. In the year-earlier period, the company earned $189,000, or two cents a share, including a special gain of $70,000, or one cent a share, on sales of $7.2 million. </TEXT></DOC>